1
00:00:00,030 --> 00:00:02,000
I learned a big lesson.

2
00:00:02,591 --> 00:00:04,721
There were many other replies.

3
00:00:05,071 --> 00:00:12,241
One fellow reported that he got in trouble with the Bureau of Internal Revenue because he used a bargain accountant.

4
00:00:12,510 --> 00:00:19,040
Another went to a cut-rate doctor and later learned he had received a completely wrong diagnosis.

5
00:00:19,390 --> 00:00:26,560
Others related the costs of going second class in home repairs, hotels, and other goods and services.

6
00:00:27,230 --> 00:00:32,641
Of course, I've heard the argument many times, but I can't afford to go first class.

7
00:00:32,830 --> 00:00:37,601
The simplest answer is, you cannot afford to go any other way.

8
00:00:38,270 --> 00:00:45,040
Certainly, in the long run, going first class actually costs you less than going second class.

9
00:00:45,390 --> 00:00:51,920
Then, too, it's better to have fewer things and have quality than to have many things and have junk.

10
00:00:52,190 --> 00:00:59,440
It's better, for example, to have one really good pair of shoes than to have three pairs of second-class shoes.

11
00:00:59,790 --> 00:01:04,081
People rate you for quality, often subconsciously, perhaps.

12
00:01:04,430 --> 00:01:06,321
Develop an instinct for quality.

13
00:01:06,430 --> 00:01:12,641
It pays, and it costs no more, often costs less, than second-class.

14
00:01:14,830 --> 00:01:18,081
Make your environment make you successful.

15
00:01:18,081 --> 00:01:19,201
1.

16
00:01:19,470 --> 00:01:21,361
Be environment-conscious.

17
00:01:21,470 --> 00:01:26,480
Just as body diet makes the body, mind diet makes the mind.

18
00:01:26,480 --> 00:01:27,520
2.

19
00:01:27,790 --> 00:01:31,040
Make your environment work for you, not against you.

20
00:01:31,230 --> 00:01:37,440
Don't let suppressive forces—the negative, you-can't-do-it people—make you think defeat.

21
00:01:37,440 --> 00:01:38,801
3.

22
00:01:39,071 --> 00:01:42,161
Don't let small-thinking people hold you back.

23
00:01:42,350 --> 00:01:45,040
Jealous people want to see you stumble.

24
00:01:45,150 --> 00:01:47,440
Don't give them that satisfaction.

25
00:01:48,031 --> 00:01:51,761
Four, get your advice from successful people.

26
00:01:51,870 --> 00:01:53,520
Your future is important.

27
00:01:53,790 --> 00:01:58,000
Never risk it with freelance advisors who are living failures.

28
00:01:59,071 --> 00:02:02,560
Five, get plenty of psychological sunshine.

29
00:02:02,670 --> 00:02:04,321
Circulate in new groups.

30
00:02:04,510 --> 00:02:07,440
Discover new and stimulating things to do.

31
00:02:08,190 --> 00:02:12,000
Six, throw thought poison out of your environment.

32
00:02:12,111 --> 00:02:13,361
Avoid gossip.

33
00:02:13,631 --> 00:02:16,801
Talk about people, but stay on the positive side.

34
00:02:16,801 --> 00:02:18,161
7.

35
00:02:18,430 --> 00:02:21,601
Go first class in everything you do.

36
00:02:21,950 --> 00:02:24,801
You can't afford to go any other way.
